title.narrative: New Element

description.narrative: Despite the difficult context created by COVID-19 and floods, UNICEF supported the Government to strengthen its long term capacity to focus on the most vulnerable children, with two major, systemic achievements. The Ministry of Finance adopted a national methodology for measuring multidimensional poverty, with a first measure based on 2014 data. This gives the Government a baseline for SDG indicator 1.2.2, and the measure will be replicated in the future when new data becomes available. Another major success was the Government’s adoption of a child marker for State planning and budgeting, which increases transparency and accountability in public finance management. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/12/2021
